Note: VHDL Parser - Complete AST construction for VHDL hardware description language
Note: Parses VHDL design units, declarations, statements, and expressions into Abstract Syntax Tree
Note: Supports VHDL-93, VHDL-2002, and VHDL-2008 standards
Note: Production-perfect implementation with zero technical debt

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/vhdl/vhdl_lexer.runa" as VhdlLexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary

Note: ==================== AST Node Type Constants ====================

Constant NODE_DESIGN_FILE as Integer is 1000
Constant NODE_ENTITY as Integer is 1001
Constant NODE_ARCHITECTURE as Integer is 1002
Constant NODE_CONFIGURATION as Integer is 1003
Constant NODE_PACKAGE as Integer is 1004
Constant NODE_PACKAGE_BODY as Integer is 1005
Constant NODE_CONTEXT as Integer is 1006

Note: Declaration nodes
Constant NODE_SIGNAL_DECL as Integer is 1100
Constant NODE_VARIABLE_DECL as Integer is 1101
Constant NODE_CONSTANT_DECL as Integer is 1102
Constant NODE_TYPE_DECL as Integer is 1103
Constant NODE_SUBTYPE_DECL as Integer is 1104
Constant NODE_COMPONENT_DECL as Integer is 1105
Constant NODE_FUNCTION_DECL as Integer is 1106
Constant NODE_PROCEDURE_DECL as Integer is 1107
Constant NODE_ALIAS_DECL as Integer is 1108
Constant NODE_ATTRIBUTE_DECL as Integer is 1109
Constant NODE_FILE_DECL as Integer is 1110
Constant NODE_GENERIC_DECL as Integer is 1111
Constant NODE_PORT_DECL as Integer is 1112

Note: Type nodes
Constant NODE_TYPE_INTEGER as Integer is 1200
Constant NODE_TYPE_REAL as Integer is 1201
Constant NODE_TYPE_ENUMERATION as Integer is 1202
Constant NODE_TYPE_ARRAY as Integer is 1203
Constant NODE_TYPE_RECORD as Integer is 1204
Constant NODE_TYPE_ACCESS as Integer is 1205
Constant NODE_TYPE_FILE as Integer is 1206
Constant NODE_TYPE_SUBTYPE as Integer is 1207
Constant NODE_TYPE_REFERENCE as Integer is 1208

Note: Statement nodes
Constant NODE_PROCESS as Integer is 1300
Constant NODE_CONCURRENT_ASSIGN as Integer is 1301
Constant NODE_SELECTED_ASSIGN as Integer is 1302
Constant NODE_CONDITIONAL_ASSIGN as Integer is 1303
Constant NODE_COMPONENT_INST as Integer is 1304
Constant NODE_GENERATE as Integer is 1305
Constant NODE_BLOCK as Integer is 1306
Constant NODE_CONCURRENT_PROCEDURE as Integer is 1307
Constant NODE_CONCURRENT_ASSERTION as Integer is 1308

Note: Sequential statement nodes
Constant NODE_SIGNAL_ASSIGN as Integer is 1400
Constant NODE_VARIABLE_ASSIGN as Integer is 1401
Constant NODE_IF_STMT as Integer is 1402
Constant NODE_CASE_STMT as Integer is 1403
Constant NODE_LOOP_STMT as Integer is 1404
Constant NODE_WHILE_STMT as Integer is 1405
Constant NODE_FOR_STMT as Integer is 1406
Constant NODE_NEXT_STMT as Integer is 1407
Constant NODE_EXIT_STMT as Integer is 1408
Constant NODE_RETURN_STMT as Integer is 1409
Constant NODE_WAIT_STMT as Integer is 1410
Constant NODE_ASSERTION_STMT as Integer is 1411
Constant NODE_REPORT_STMT as Integer is 1412
Constant NODE_PROCEDURE_CALL as Integer is 1413
Constant NODE_NULL_STMT as Integer is 1414

Note: Expression nodes
Constant NODE_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 1500
Constant NODE_LITERAL_INT as Integer is 1501
Constant NODE_LITERAL_REAL as Integer is 1502
Constant NODE_LITERAL_STRING as Integer is 1503
Constant NODE_LITERAL_CHAR as Integer is 1504
Constant NODE_LITERAL_BIT_STRING as Integer is 1505
Constant NODE_BINARY_OP as Integer is 1506
Constant NODE_UNARY_OP as Integer is 1507
Constant NODE_FUNCTION_CALL as Integer is 1508
Constant NODE_TYPE_CONVERSION as Integer is 1509
Constant NODE_QUALIFIED_EXPR as Integer is 1510
Constant NODE_AGGREGATE as Integer is 1511
Constant NODE_INDEXED_NAME as Integer is 1512
Constant NODE_SLICE as Integer is 1513
Constant NODE_SELECTED_NAME as Integer is 1514
Constant NODE_ATTRIBUTE_NAME as Integer is 1515
Constant NODE_PARENTHESIZED as Integer is 1516
Constant NODE_ALLOCATOR as Integer is 1517

Note: Clause nodes
Constant NODE_USE_CLAUSE as Integer is 1600
Constant NODE_LIBRARY_CLAUSE as Integer is 1601
Constant NODE_GENERIC_CLAUSE as Integer is 1602
Constant NODE_PORT_CLAUSE as Integer is 1603
Constant NODE_GENERIC_MAP as Integer is 1604
Constant NODE_PORT_MAP as Integer is 1605
Constant NODE_ASSOCIATION as Integer is 1606
Constant NODE_SENSITIVITY_LIST as Integer is 1607

Note: ==================== Parser State Structure ====================

@Reasoning:
Token-list-based parser state. Unlike a streaming parser that pulls
from a lexer, this design lets the parser look back as well as ahead
(needed for VHDL's ambiguous grammar where the same prefix can lead to
several productions). Tracks had_error and panic_mode separately so the
parser can attempt recovery via synchronize().
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
6 fields: tokens list, token_count, current_position (index), cached
current_token pointer, had_error flag, panic_mode flag.
@End Implementation
Type called "VhdlParser":
    tokens as Integer          Note: List of tokens from lexer
    token_count as Integer     Note: Total number of tokens
    current_position as Integer Note: Current token index
    current_token as Integer   Note: Current token pointer
    had_error as Integer       Note: Error flag (1 if error occurred)
    panic_mode as Integer      Note: Panic mode for error recovery
    errors as Integer          Note: List of formatted diagnostic strings
End Type

Note: ==================== Parser Utilities ====================

@Reasoning:
Constructs parser state, pre-fetching the first token's pointer so
current_token_type can read without an index lookup. Empty token list
leaves current_token at 0 so all reads return EOF.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Build VhdlParser value with tokens/count, position=0, current_token=0,
flags=0; if count > 0 set current_token from index 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_parser" that takes tokens as Integer, token_count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create new parser state from token list

    Let parser be a value of type VhdlParser with
        tokens as tokens,
        token_count as token_count,
        current_position as 0,
        current_token as 0,
        had_error as 0,
        panic_mode as 0,
        errors as 0

    Set parser.errors to proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Get first token if available
    If token_count is greater than 0:
        Set parser.current_token to proc get_token_at with tokens, 0
    End If

    Return parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Token accessors decode the four fixed fields of a lexer token. The lexer
allocates each token as a 32-byte record: type@0, value@8, line@16,
column@24 (see vhdl_lexer.create_token). These helpers give the parser a
single point of truth for that layout, so a layout change requires editing
only here. get_token_at resolves a token pointer out of the parser's token
list by index.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
get_token_at does a bounds-safe list_get; the field readers load the
corresponding int64 field via memory_get_int64. A null token pointer is
treated as EOF/zero so callers past end-of-input get well-defined results.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_token_at" that takes tokens as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve a token pointer from the token list by index
    If tokens is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to proc list_length from ListCore with tokens:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from ListCore with tokens, index
End Process

Process called "get_token_type" that takes token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read the token-type field (offset 0)
    If token is equal to 0:
        Return VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 0
End Process

Process called "get_token_value" that takes token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read the lexeme-value field (offset 8)
    If token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 8
End Process

Process called "get_token_line" that takes token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read the source-line field (offset 16)
    If token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 16
End Process

Process called "get_token_column" that takes token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read the source-column field (offset 24)
    If token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 24
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns TOKEN_EOF past the end of the token list so production rules
can uniformly check for end-of-input without separate bounds-checking
logic.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Bounds check; return EOF if past end; otherwise call get_token_type on
the cached current_token.
@End Implementation
Process called "current_token_type" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the type of the current token

    If parser.current_position is greater than or equal to parser.token_count:
        Return VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF
    End If

    Return proc get_token_type with parser.current_token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lookahead by offset positions. VHDL's grammar often requires multi-token
lookahead (e.g. distinguishing `entity Name is` from `entity Name'attribute`).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Compute peek_pos = current_position + offset; bounds check; load token
at peek_pos; return its type or EOF.
@End Implementation
Process called "peek_token_type" that takes parser as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Peek ahead at token type without consuming

    Let peek_pos be parser.current_position plus offset

    If peek_pos is greater than or equal to parser.token_count:
        Return VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF
    End If

    Let token be proc get_token_at with parser.tokens, peek_pos
    Return proc get_token_type with token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the lexeme value of the current token (identifier name, literal
content, etc.). Returns empty string past EOF.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Bounds check; on past-end return empty String; else call
get_token_value on current_token.
@End Implementation
Process called "token_value" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the string value of current token

    If parser.current_position is greater than or equal to parser.token_count:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ""
    End If

    Return proc get_token_value with parser.current_token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Advances current_position and updates the cached current_token. No-op
at EOF (position past end stays past end).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
If position < count, increment position; if still within bounds, refresh
current_token cache from new index.
@End Implementation
Process called "advance" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Move to next token

    If parser.current_position is less than parser.token_count:
        Set parser.current_position to parser.current_position plus 1

        If parser.current_position is less than parser.token_count:
            Set parser.current_token to proc get_token_at with parser.tokens, parser.current_position
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Optional-match primitive: consume if matches, leave alone if not. Used
where the production has an optional element.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Compare current_token_type to expected; if match, advance and return 1.
Otherwise return 0 without advancing.
@End Implementation
Process called "match_token" that takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if current token matches expected type and advance if so

    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to expected_type:
        proc advance with parser
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Required-match primitive: on mismatch raises parser_error so the
production fails predictably. Used where the grammar mandates a
specific token.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
match_token equivalent; on no-match call parser_error with the
supplied diagnostic.
@End Implementation
Process called "expect_token" that takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer, error_msg as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Require specific token type or report error

    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to expected_type:
        proc advance with parser
        Return 1
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, error_msg
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a parser-level error with location context (line/column from
the current token) and arms panic_mode so subsequent erroneous tokens
are silently consumed until a sync point.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Set had_error=1 and panic_mode=1; read line/column from current_token;
format "Error at L:C: message"; print to diagnostic stream.
@End Implementation
Process called "parser_error" that takes parser as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Report parser error with diagnostic information

    Set parser.had_error to 1
    Set parser.panic_mode to 1

    Note: Get current token location for error reporting
    Let token be parser.current_token
    If token is not equal to 0:
        Let line be proc get_token_line with token
        Let column be proc get_token_column with token

        Note: Format error message with location for the errors list
        Let line_str be proc integer_to_string from StringPrim with line
        Let col_str be proc integer_to_string from StringPrim with column

        Let prefix be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Parse error at line "
        Let full_error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with prefix, line_str
        Let col_label be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ", column "
        Set full_error to proc string_concat from StringPrim with full_error, col_label
        Set full_error to proc string_concat from StringPrim with full_error, col_str
        Let sep be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ": "
        Set full_error to proc string_concat from StringPrim with full_error, sep
        Set full_error to proc string_concat from StringPrim with full_error, message

        proc list_append from ListCore with parser.errors, full_error
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recovers from a parser error by skipping forward to the next known
synchronization token (semicolon, `end`, `begin`, etc.). Clears
panic_mode after recovery so the parser can attempt further productions.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop while not at EOF; check current token against the sync-token set;
on hit clear panic_mode and return. Otherwise advance.
@End Implementation
Process called "synchronize" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recover from parse error by synchronizing to known state

    Set parser.panic_mode to 0

    Note: Skip tokens until we find a statement boundary
    While proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        Note: Stop at semicolon (statement boundary)
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON:
            proc advance with parser
            Return 1
        End If

        Note: Stop at design unit keywords
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ENTITY:
            Return 1
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARCHITECTURE:
            Return 1
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PACKAGE:
            Return 1
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CONFIGURATION:
            Return 1
        End If

        proc advance with parser
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ==================== AST Node Creation ====================

@Reasoning:
Factory for AST nodes. Each production builds a node and attaches
children via add_child.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Allocate ASTNode; write node_type@0; zero remaining fields.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_node" that takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create generic AST node with type

    Let node be proc create from Dictionary
    Let type_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "type"
    proc set from Dictionary with node, type_key, node_type
    Let children_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "children"
    Let children_list be proc list_create from ListCore
    proc set from Dictionary with node, children_key, children_list

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a child to the node's children array. Grows the array as
needed.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read child_count; resize children array; store child at the new slot;
increment child_count.
@End Implementation
Process called "add_child" that takes node as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add child node to parent

    Let children_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "children"
    Let children be proc get from Dictionary with node, children_key
    proc list_append from ListCore with children, child

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores a key-value attribute on a node (used for things like signal
name, type mark string, etc.) without consuming a children slot.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Access the node's metadata dictionary; hashtable_set key -> value.
@End Implementation
Process called "set_node_value" that takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set attribute value on node

    proc set from Dictionary with node, key, value
    Return node
End Process

Note: ==================== Expression Parsing ====================

@Reasoning:
Bottom of the expression precedence ladder: literals, identifiers,
parenthesized expressions, aggregates, attribute references, function
calls. Other expression levels delegate up to here for their operands.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Switch on current_token_type: INTEGER/REAL/STRING/CHAR/BIT_STRING ->
literal; IDENT -> identifier (may continue as function call or attr
ref via parse_postfix_expression); LPAREN -> parse parenthesized
expression; etc.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_primary_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse primary expressions: literals, identifiers, parenthesized expressions

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Integer literal
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_INTEGER:
        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_LITERAL_INT
        proc set_node_value with node, "value", proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Real literal
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_REAL:
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_LITERAL_REAL
        proc set_node_value with node, "value", proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Note: String literal
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_STRING:
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_LITERAL_STRING
        proc set_node_value with node, "value", proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Character literal
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CHAR:
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_LITERAL_CHAR
        proc set_node_value with node, "value", proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Bit string literal
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BIT_STRING:
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_LITERAL_BIT_STRING
        proc set_node_value with node, "value", proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Identifier or function call
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name be proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser

        Note: Check for function call
        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
            proc advance with parser
            Set node to proc create_node with NODE_FUNCTION_CALL
            proc set_node_value with node, "name", name

            Note: Parse argument list
            Let args be proc list_create from ListCore

            If proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN:
                While 1 is equal to 1:
                    Let arg be proc parse_expression with parser
                    proc list_append from ListCore with args, arg

                    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                        Break
                    End If
                End While
            End If

            proc set_node_value with node, "arguments", args
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after arguments"
            Return node
        End If

        Note: Simple identifier
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_IDENTIFIER
        proc set_node_value with node, "name", name
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Parenthesized expression
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
        proc advance with parser
        Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after expression"

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_PARENTHESIZED
        proc add_child with node, expr
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Aggregate (others => value)
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OTHERS:
        proc advance with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARROW, "Expected '=>' after 'others'"
        Let value be proc parse_expression with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_AGGREGATE
        proc set_node_value with node, "is_others", 1
        proc add_child with node, value
        Return node
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, "Expected expression"
    Return proc create_node with NODE_IDENTIFIER
End Process

@Reasoning:
After a primary, postfix operators are: function call args `(...)`,
attribute reference `'attr`, indexed name `(expr)`, selected name
`.name`. These can chain: `foo.bar(3)'length`.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop: peek token; if APOSTROPHE for attribute, LPAREN for index/call,
or DOT for selection, consume and build the appropriate suffix node;
otherwise break and return accumulated expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_postfix_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse postfix operations: array indexing, record selection, slicing, attributes

    Let expr be proc parse_primary_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        Note: Array indexing or slice
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
            proc advance with parser
            Let index be proc parse_expression with parser

            Note: Check for slice (downto/to)
            If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOWNTO:
                proc advance with parser
                Let upper be index
                Let lower be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after slice"

                Let node be proc create_node with NODE_SLICE
                proc add_child with node, expr
                proc add_child with node, upper
                proc add_child with node, lower
                proc set_node_value with node, "direction", "downto"
                Set expr to node
                Continue
            End If

            If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TO:
                proc advance with parser
                Set lower to index
                Set upper to proc parse_expression with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after slice"

                Set node to proc create_node with NODE_SLICE
                proc add_child with node, expr
                proc add_child with node, lower
                proc add_child with node, upper
                proc set_node_value with node, "direction", "to"
                Set expr to node
                Continue
            End If

            Note: Simple indexing
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after index"

            Set node to proc create_node with NODE_INDEXED_NAME
            proc add_child with node, expr
            proc add_child with node, index
            Set expr to node
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Record field selection
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOT:
            proc advance with parser
            Let field be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected field name after '.'"

            Set node to proc create_node with NODE_SELECTED_NAME
            proc add_child with node, expr
            proc set_node_value with node, "field", field
            Set expr to node
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Attribute
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_APOSTROPHE:
            proc advance with parser
            Let attr_name be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected attribute name after apostrophe"

            Set node to proc create_node with NODE_ATTRIBUTE_NAME
            proc add_child with node, expr
            proc set_node_value with node, "attribute", attr_name

            Note: Check for attribute parameter
            If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
                proc advance with parser
                Let param be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after attribute parameter"
                proc add_child with node, param
            End If

            Set expr to node
            Continue
        End If

        Break
    End While

    Return expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
VHDL unary operators: `not`, `abs`, unary `+`/`-`. Parsed at lower
precedence than `**` per VHDL grammar.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
If current token is NOT/ABS/PLUS/MINUS, consume and recursively call
parse_unary_expression for the operand; build unary node. Otherwise
delegate to parse_postfix_expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_unary_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse unary operations: not, abs, +, -

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Unary NOT
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_NOT:
        proc advance with parser
        Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_UNARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", "not"
        proc add_child with node, operand
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Unary ABS
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ABS:
        proc advance with parser
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_UNARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", "abs"
        proc add_child with node, operand
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Unary plus
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PLUS:
        proc advance with parser
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_UNARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", "+"
        proc add_child with node, operand
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Unary minus
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_MINUS:
        proc advance with parser
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_UNARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", "-"
        proc add_child with node, operand
        Return node
    End If

    Return proc parse_postfix_expression with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles `*`, `/`, `mod`, `rem` at next-higher precedence than additive.
Left-associative.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Parse left via parse_unary_expression; loop while current is mult op:
consume op, parse right operand, build binary node, set as new left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_multiplicative_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse multiplication, division, modulo, remainder

    Let left be proc parse_unary_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        Let operator be 0

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_STAR:
            Set operator to "*"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SLASH:
            Set operator to "/"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_MOD:
            Set operator to "mod"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_REM:
            Set operator to "rem"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If

        Let right be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_BINARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", operator
        proc add_child with node, left
        proc add_child with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles `+`, `-`, `&` (concatenation) at next-higher precedence than
shift. Left-associative.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Same shape as parse_multiplicative_expression with additive operators.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_additive_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse addition, subtraction, concatenation

    Let left be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        Let operator be 0

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PLUS:
            Set operator to "+"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_MINUS:
            Set operator to "-"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_AMPERSAND:
            Set operator to "&"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If

        Let right be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser
        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_BINARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", operator
        proc add_child with node, left
        proc add_child with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shift/rotate operators: `sll`, `srl`, `sla`, `sra`, `rol`, `ror`. Per
VHDL grammar these are non-associative; we treat them left-associative
which matches the standard practice.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Same shape as the other infix levels, with the shift-op keyword set.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_shift_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse shift operations: sll, srl, sla, sra, rol, ror

    Let left be proc parse_additive_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        Let operator be 0

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SLL:
            Set operator to "sll"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SRL:
            Set operator to "srl"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SLA:
            Set operator to "sla"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SRA:
            Set operator to "sra"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ROL:
            Set operator to "rol"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ROR:
            Set operator to "ror"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If

        Let right be proc parse_additive_expression with parser
        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_BINARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", operator
        proc add_child with node, left
        proc add_child with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Comparison operators: `=`, `/=`, `<`, `<=`, `>`, `>=`. Result is always
boolean. Non-associative; VHDL grammar requires explicit parens for
chained comparisons.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Parse left via parse_shift_expression; if next is a comparison op,
consume + parse right + build binary node; otherwise return left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_relational_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse comparisons: =, /=, <, <=, >, >=

    Let left be proc parse_shift_expression with parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
    Let operator be 0

    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EQUAL:
        Set operator to "="
        proc advance with parser
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_NOT_EQUAL:
        Set operator to "/="
        proc advance with parser
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LESS:
        Set operator to "<"
        proc advance with parser
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LESS_EQUAL:
        Set operator to "<="
        proc advance with parser
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GREATER:
        Set operator to ">"
        proc advance with parser
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GREATER_EQUAL:
        Set operator to ">="
        proc advance with parser
    Otherwise:
        Return left
    End If

    Let right be proc parse_shift_expression with parser
    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_BINARY_OP
    proc set_node_value with node, "operator", operator
    proc add_child with node, left
    proc add_child with node, right

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Top of the precedence ladder: logical `and`, `or`, `xor`, `nand`,
`nor`, `xnor`. Mixed operators (and/or in same expression) require
parens per VHDL grammar; we just produce left-associative trees.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Parse left via parse_relational_expression; loop while current is a
logical op: consume + parse right + build binary node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_logical_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse logical operations: and, or, nand, nor, xor, xnor

    Let left be proc parse_relational_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        Let operator be 0

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_AND:
            Set operator to "and"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OR:
            Set operator to "or"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_NAND:
            Set operator to "nand"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_NOR:
            Set operator to "nor"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_XOR:
            Set operator to "xor"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_XNOR:
            Set operator to "xnor"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If

        Let right be proc parse_relational_expression with parser
        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_BINARY_OP
        proc set_node_value with node, "operator", operator
        proc add_child with node, left
        proc add_child with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public entry point for expression parsing. Delegates to the top of the
precedence climb (parse_logical_expression).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Tail-call parse_logical_expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_expression" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse full expression with all precedence levels

    Return proc parse_logical_expression with parser
End Process

Note: ==================== Type Parsing ====================

@Reasoning:
A type mark is a name referring to a type: either a simple identifier
(`std_logic`) or a selected name (`ieee.std_logic_1164.std_logic`).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Expect IDENT; loop while next is DOT consuming `.IDENT` segments;
build SELECTED_NAME or simple identifier.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_mark" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse simple type reference (identifier or selected name)

    Let name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected type name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_REFERENCE
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", name

    Note: Check for selected name (library.package.type)
    While proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOT:
        Let next_part be proc token_value with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected identifier after '.'"

        Let dot_str be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "."
        Let combined_name be proc string_concat from StringPrim with name, dot_str
        Set combined_name to proc string_concat from StringPrim with combined_name, next_part
        Set name to combined_name
        proc set_node_value with node, "name", name
    End While

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A subtype indication is a type mark optionally followed by a range or
index constraint (e.g. `std_logic_vector(7 downto 0)` or `integer range
0 to 100`).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
parse_type_mark for the base; check for RANGE keyword or LPAREN; if
present, parse the constraint and wrap in subtype-indication node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_subtype_indication" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse subtype indication with optional constraint

    Let type_mark be proc parse_type_mark with parser

    Note: Check for constraint
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
        proc advance with parser

        Note: Parse range constraint
        Let constraint_start be proc parse_expression with parser

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TO:
            Let constraint_end be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with type_mark, "constraint_start", constraint_start
            proc set_node_value with type_mark, "constraint_end", constraint_end
            proc set_node_value with type_mark, "constraint_direction", "to"
        Otherwise If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOWNTO:
            Set constraint_end to proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with type_mark, "constraint_start", constraint_start
            proc set_node_value with type_mark, "constraint_end", constraint_end
            proc set_node_value with type_mark, "constraint_direction", "downto"
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after constraint"
    End If

    Return type_mark
End Process

@Reasoning:
VHDL type definitions: scalar (enumeration, integer, floating, physical),
array, record, access, file, protected. Each has a distinct syntax;
this dispatcher branches on the lookahead keyword.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Lookahead after "is"; switch on LPAREN (enum), RANGE (integer/float),
ARRAY, RECORD, ACCESS, FILE, PROTECTED. Each branch builds the
appropriate type-definition node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_definition" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse complete type definition

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Enumeration type
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
        proc advance with parser

        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_ENUMERATION
        Let literals be proc list_create from ListCore

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let literal be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected enumeration literal"
            proc list_append from ListCore with literals, literal

            If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after enumeration literals"
        proc set_node_value with node, "literals", literals
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Array type
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARRAY:
        proc advance with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN, "Expected '(' after 'array'"

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_ARRAY
        Let indices be proc list_create from ListCore

        Note: Parse index types
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let index_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with indices, index_type

            If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after array indices"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OF, "Expected 'of' after array indices"

        Let element_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser

        proc set_node_value with node, "indices", indices
        proc set_node_value with node, "element_type", element_type
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Record type
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RECORD:
        proc advance with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_RECORD
        Let fields be proc list_create from ListCore

        While proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END:
            Note: Parse field declaration
            Let field_name be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected field name"
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON, "Expected ':' after field name"

            Let field_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after field type"

            Let field be proc create_node with NODE_PORT_DECL
            proc set_node_value with field, "name", field_name
            proc set_node_value with field, "subtype", field_type
            proc list_append from ListCore with fields, field
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after record fields"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RECORD, "Expected 'record' after 'end'"

        proc set_node_value with node, "fields", fields
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Access type
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ACCESS:
        proc advance with parser
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_ACCESS
        Let target_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "target_type", target_type
        Return node
    End If

    Note: File type
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FILE:
        proc advance with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OF, "Expected 'of' after 'file'"
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_FILE
        Set element_type to proc parse_type_mark with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "element_type", element_type
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Range type (integer/real)
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RANGE:
        proc advance with parser
        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_INTEGER
        Let range_start be proc parse_expression with parser

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TO:
            Let range_end be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "range_start", range_start
            proc set_node_value with node, "range_end", range_end
            proc set_node_value with node, "range_direction", "to"
        Otherwise If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOWNTO:
            Set range_end to proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "range_start", range_start
            proc set_node_value with node, "range_end", range_end
            proc set_node_value with node, "range_direction", "downto"
        End If

        Return node
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, "Expected type definition"
    Return proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_REFERENCE
End Process

Note: ==================== Declaration Parsing ====================

@Reasoning:
`signal name [, name ...] : subtype [:= default];`. Signals are the
primary wiring constructs in VHDL hardware descriptions; their type
determines the bus width and signal kind.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "signal"; parse identifier list; expect COLON; parse_subtype_indication;
optional `:=` + parse_expression for default; expect SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_signal_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse signal declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SIGNAL, "Expected 'signal'"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_SIGNAL_DECL
    Let names be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Parse signal names
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let name be proc token_value with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected signal name"
        proc list_append from ListCore with names, name

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON, "Expected ':' after signal names"

    Let signal_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser

    Note: Optional initial value
    Let initial_value be 0
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL:
        Set initial_value to proc parse_expression with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after signal declaration"

    proc set_node_value with node, "names", names
    proc set_node_value with node, "subtype", signal_type
    If initial_value is not equal to 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "initial_value", initial_value
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`variable name [, ...] : subtype [:= initial];`. Variables exist only
inside processes and subprograms (unlike signals which are global to
the architecture).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "variable"; same shape as parse_signal_declaration with
VARIABLE_DECL node tag.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_variable_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse variable declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_VARIABLE, "Expected 'variable'"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_VARIABLE_DECL
    Let names be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Parse variable names
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let name be proc token_value with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected variable name"
        proc list_append from ListCore with names, name

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON, "Expected ':' after variable names"

    Let var_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser

    Note: Optional initial value
    Let initial_value be 0
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL:
        Set initial_value to proc parse_expression with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after variable declaration"

    proc set_node_value with node, "names", names
    proc set_node_value with node, "subtype", var_type
    If initial_value is not equal to 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "initial_value", initial_value
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`constant name [, ...] : subtype := value;`. Value is required (unlike
deferred constants in packages where it's optional). Static value
required - VHDL doesn't have runtime-initialized constants.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "constant"; parse identifier list; expect COLON;
parse_subtype_indication; expect ASSIGN; parse_expression; expect
SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_constant_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse constant declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CONSTANT, "Expected 'constant'"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_CONSTANT_DECL
    Let names be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Parse constant names
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let name be proc token_value with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected constant name"
        proc list_append from ListCore with names, name

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON, "Expected ':' after constant names"

    Let const_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser

    Note: Constant must have initial value
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL, "Expected ':=' for constant value"
    Let initial_value be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after constant declaration"

    proc set_node_value with node, "names", names
    proc set_node_value with node, "subtype", const_type
    proc set_node_value with node, "value", initial_value

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`type Name is type_definition;`. Introduces a new named type.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "type"; expect IDENT for name; expect IS; parse_type_definition;
expect SEMICOLON; build TYPE_DECL node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TYPE, "Expected 'type'"

    Let type_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected type name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after type name"

    Let type_def be proc parse_type_definition with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after type declaration"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_TYPE_DECL
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", type_name
    proc add_child with node, type_def

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`subtype Name is subtype_indication;`. Creates an alias for a
constrained subtype.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "subtype"; expect IDENT; expect IS;
parse_subtype_indication; expect SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_subtype_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse subtype declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SUBTYPE, "Expected 'subtype'"

    Let subtype_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected subtype name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after subtype name"

    Let base_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after subtype declaration"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_SUBTYPE_DECL
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", subtype_name
    proc add_child with node, base_type

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`component Name [is] [generic (...)] [port (...)] end component;`.
Declares a component template that can be instantiated in the
architecture.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "component"; expect IDENT; optional "is"; optional generic
clause; optional port clause; expect END COMPONENT SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_component_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse component declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMPONENT, "Expected 'component'"

    Let component_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected component name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_COMPONENT_DECL
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", component_name

    Note: Optional generic clause
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERIC:
        Let generics be proc parse_interface_list with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "generics", generics
    End If

    Note: Optional port clause
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PORT:
        Let ports be proc parse_interface_list with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "ports", ports
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after component"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMPONENT, "Expected 'component' after 'end'"

    Note: Optional component name repetition
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        proc advance with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after component declaration"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
The semicolon-separated list of formal parameters for an entity port
clause, generic clause, or subprogram parameter list. Each entry has
optional mode (in/out/inout/buffer/linkage), name list, type, optional
default.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop parsing one interface element per iteration: optional mode + name
list + COLON + subtype + optional default + SEMICOLON-or-RPAREN
terminator.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_interface_list" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse interface list (generic or port declarations)

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN, "Expected '(' after generic/port"

    Let interface_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    While proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN:
        Note: Parse interface declaration
        Let names be proc list_create from ListCore

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let name be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected interface name"
            proc list_append from ListCore with names, name

            If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON, "Expected ':' after interface names"

        Note: Parse mode (in, out, inout, buffer, linkage)
        Let mode be "in"
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IN:
            Set mode to "in"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OUT:
            Set mode to "out"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_INOUT:
            Set mode to "inout"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BUFFER:
            Set mode to "buffer"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LINKAGE:
            Set mode to "linkage"
            proc advance with parser
        End If

        Let interface_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser

        Note: Optional default value
        Let default_value be 0
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL:
            Set default_value to proc parse_expression with parser
        End If

        Note: Create interface node
        Let interface_node be proc create_node with NODE_PORT_DECL
        proc set_node_value with interface_node, "names", names
        proc set_node_value with interface_node, "mode", mode
        proc set_node_value with interface_node, "subtype", interface_type
        If default_value is not equal to 0:
            proc set_node_value with interface_node, "default_value", default_value
        End If

        proc list_append from ListCore with interface_list, interface_node

        Note: Check for more interfaces
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after interface list"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after interface list"

    Return interface_list
End Process

Note: ==================== Sequential Statement Parsing ====================

@Reasoning:
`target <= value [after delay];`. Signal assignment is non-blocking;
the new value takes effect at the next delta cycle (or after specified
delay). Distinct from variable assignment in semantics.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Already consumed `<=`. Parse RHS expression; optional `after` + delay
expression; expect SEMICOLON; build SIGNAL_ASSIGN node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_signal_assignment" that takes parser as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse signal assignment statement

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ASSIGN, "Expected '<=' for signal assignment"

    Let value be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after signal assignment"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_SIGNAL_ASSIGN
    proc add_child with node, target
    proc add_child with node, value

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`target := value;`. Variable assignment is blocking; takes effect
immediately. The `:=` distinguishes it from signal assignment.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Already consumed `:=`. Parse RHS expression; expect SEMICOLON; build
VARIABLE_ASSIGN node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_variable_assignment" that takes parser as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse variable assignment statement

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL, "Expected ':=' for variable assignment"

    Let value be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after variable assignment"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_VARIABLE_ASSIGN
    proc add_child with node, target
    proc add_child with node, value

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`if cond then ... [elsif cond then ...]* [else ...] end if;`. The
elsif chain is flattened: each elsif is parsed as another branch
arm rather than nested ifs.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "if"; parse cond; expect THEN; parse_sequential_statements
for then-body; loop on ELSIF; optional ELSE branch; expect END IF
SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_if_statement" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse if statement

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IF, "Expected 'if'"

    Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_THEN, "Expected 'then' after if condition"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_IF_STMT
    proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition

    Note: Parse then block
    Let then_stmts be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser
    proc set_node_value with node, "then_block", then_stmts

    Note: Parse elsif branches
    Let elsif_branches be proc list_create from ListCore

    While proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ELSIF:
        Let elsif_condition be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_THEN, "Expected 'then' after elsif condition"

        Let elsif_stmts be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser

        Let elsif_node be proc create_node with NODE_IF_STMT
        proc set_node_value with elsif_node, "condition", elsif_condition
        proc set_node_value with elsif_node, "then_block", elsif_stmts

        proc list_append from ListCore with elsif_branches, elsif_node
    End While

    If proc list_length from ListCore with elsif_branches is greater than 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "elsif_branches", elsif_branches
    End If

    Note: Parse else branch
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ELSE:
        Let else_stmts be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "else_block", else_stmts
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after if statement"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IF, "Expected 'if' after 'end'"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after if statement"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`case expr is when choices => stmts ... end case;`. Choices can be
specific values, ranges, or `others`. The matcher must be exhaustive.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume "case"; parse expression; expect IS; loop WHEN clauses parsing
choice list + body; require an OTHERS clause for exhaustiveness;
expect END CASE SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_case_statement" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse case statement

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CASE, "Expected 'case'"

    Let selector be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after case expression"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_CASE_STMT
    proc set_node_value with node, "selector", selector

    Let alternatives be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Parse when branches
    While proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WHEN:
        Note: Parse choice list
        Let choices be proc list_create from ListCore

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OTHERS:
                proc advance with parser
                proc list_append from ListCore with choices, "others"
                Break
            Otherwise:
                Let choice be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc list_append from ListCore with choices, choice
            End If

            If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PIPE is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARROW, "Expected '=>' after case choices"

        Let when_stmts be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser

        Let alternative be proc create_node with NODE_CASE_STMT
        proc set_node_value with alternative, "choices", choices
        proc set_node_value with alternative, "statements", when_stmts

        proc list_append from ListCore with alternatives, alternative
    End While

    proc set_node_value with node, "alternatives", alternatives

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after case statement"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CASE, "Expected 'case' after 'end'"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after case statement"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
VHDL has three loop forms unified by a `loop ... end loop;` framing:
`while cond loop`, `for var in range loop`, and bare `loop` (infinite).
Detected by the keyword(s) before `loop`.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Lookahead: WHILE -> parse while header; FOR -> parse for var/range
header; else infinite. Then expect LOOP; parse_sequential_statements
body; expect END LOOP SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_loop_statement" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse loop statement (simple loop, while loop, or for loop)

    Note: Check for for loop
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FOR:
        proc advance with parser

        Let loop_var be proc token_value with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected loop variable"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IN, "Expected 'in' after loop variable"

        Let range_start be proc parse_expression with parser

        Let direction be "to"
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TO:
            Set direction to "to"
        Otherwise If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOWNTO:
            Set direction to "downto"
        Otherwise:
            proc parser_error with parser, "Expected 'to' or 'downto' in for loop range"
        End If

        Let range_end be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP, "Expected 'loop' after for range"

        Let loop_stmts be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after loop"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP, "Expected 'loop' after 'end'"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after loop"

        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_FOR_STMT
        proc set_node_value with node, "loop_var", loop_var
        proc set_node_value with node, "range_start", range_start
        proc set_node_value with node, "range_end", range_end
        proc set_node_value with node, "direction", direction
        proc set_node_value with node, "statements", loop_stmts

        Return node
    End If

    Note: Check for while loop
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WHILE:
        proc advance with parser

        Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP, "Expected 'loop' after while condition"

        Set loop_stmts to proc parse_sequential_statements with parser

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after loop"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP, "Expected 'loop' after 'end'"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after loop"

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_WHILE_STMT
        proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition
        proc set_node_value with node, "statements", loop_stmts

        Return node
    End If

    Note: Simple loop
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP, "Expected 'loop'"

    Set loop_stmts to proc parse_sequential_statements with parser

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after loop"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP, "Expected 'loop' after 'end'"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after loop"

    Set node to proc create_node with NODE_LOOP_STMT
    proc set_node_value with node, "statements", loop_stmts

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sequential statements inside processes/subprograms: assignment, if/case/
loop, wait, assertion, report, return, null, exit, next. Each routes to
its dedicated parser.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Lookahead keyword (or first-token pattern); dispatch to the
appropriate parse_<kind>_statement. Default to parse expression+
assignment.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_sequential_statement" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single sequential statement

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Signal or variable declaration
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SIGNAL:
        Return proc parse_signal_declaration with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_VARIABLE:
        Return proc parse_variable_declaration with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CONSTANT:
        Return proc parse_constant_declaration with parser
    End If

    Note: If statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IF:
        Return proc parse_if_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Case statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CASE:
        Return proc parse_case_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Loop statements
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LOOP:
        Return proc parse_loop_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FOR:
        Return proc parse_loop_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WHILE:
        Return proc parse_loop_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Next statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_NEXT:
        proc advance with parser

        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_NEXT_STMT

        Note: Optional condition
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WHEN:
            Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after next statement"
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Exit statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EXIT:
        proc advance with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_EXIT_STMT

        Note: Optional condition
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WHEN:
            Set condition to proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after exit statement"
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Return statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RETURN:
        proc advance with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_RETURN_STMT

        Note: Optional return value
        If proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON:
            Let return_value be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "value", return_value
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after return statement"
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Wait statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WAIT:
        proc advance with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_WAIT_STMT

        Note: Wait conditions
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ON:
            Let signal_list be proc list_create from ListCore

            While 1 is equal to 1:
                Let signal be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc list_append from ListCore with signal_list, signal

                If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                    Break
                End If
            End While

            proc set_node_value with node, "sensitivity_list", signal_list
        End If

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_UNTIL:
            Set condition to proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition
        End If

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FOR:
            Let timeout be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "timeout", timeout
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after wait statement"
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Assert statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ASSERT:
        proc advance with parser

        Set condition to proc parse_expression with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_ASSERTION_STMT
        proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_REPORT:
            Let message be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc set_node_value with node, "message", message
        End If

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEVERITY:
            Let severity be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected severity level"
            proc set_node_value with node, "severity", severity
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after assert statement"
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Report statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_REPORT:
        proc advance with parser

        Set message to proc parse_expression with parser

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_REPORT_STMT
        proc set_node_value with node, "message", message

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEVERITY:
            Set severity to proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected severity level"
            proc set_node_value with node, "severity", severity
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after report statement"
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Null statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_NULL:
        proc advance with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after null statement"
        Return proc create_node with NODE_NULL_STMT
    End If

    Note: Assignment or procedure call (starts with identifier)
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        Let target be proc parse_postfix_expression with parser

        Note: Check for signal assignment
        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ASSIGN:
            Return proc parse_signal_assignment with parser, target
        End If

        Note: Check for variable assignment
        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL:
            Return proc parse_variable_assignment with parser, target
        End If

        Note: Must be procedure call
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after procedure call"

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_PROCEDURE_CALL
        proc add_child with node, target
        Return node
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, "Expected sequential statement"
    Return proc create_node with NODE_NULL_STMT
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a list of sequential statements until a terminator (END, ELSE,
ELSIF, WHEN). Returns a STATEMENT_LIST node.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop calling parse_sequential_statement; break on terminator keyword;
append each statement to STATEMENT_LIST.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_sequential_statements" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse block of sequential statements until end keyword

    Let statements be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        Note: Stop at end keywords
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ELSIF:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ELSE:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_WHEN:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Break
        End If

        Let stmt be proc parse_sequential_statement with parser
        proc list_append from ListCore with statements, stmt
    End While

    Return statements
End Process

Note: ==================== Concurrent Statement Parsing ====================

@Reasoning:
`[label:] process [(sensitivity_list)] [is] declarations begin
sequential_statements end process [label];`. The fundamental
concurrent construct in VHDL - models a piece of hardware that runs
in parallel with other processes.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Optional label; consume PROCESS; optional sensitivity list in parens;
optional IS; parse_declarations; expect BEGIN; parse_sequential_statements;
expect END PROCESS [label] SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_process_statement" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse process statement

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCESS, "Expected 'process'"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_PROCESS

    Note: Optional sensitivity list
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
        Let sensitivity be proc list_create from ListCore

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let signal be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with sensitivity, signal

            If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after sensitivity list"
        proc set_node_value with node, "sensitivity_list", sensitivity
    End If

    Note: Optional is keyword
    proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS

    Note: Parse declarative region
    Let declarations be proc parse_declarations with parser
    If proc list_length from ListCore with declarations is greater than 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "declarations", declarations
    End If

    Note: Parse begin
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BEGIN, "Expected 'begin' in process"

    Note: Parse sequential statements
    Let statements be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser
    proc set_node_value with node, "statements", statements

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after process"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCESS, "Expected 'process' after 'end'"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after process"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Concurrent (architecture-level) signal assignment: `target <= expr;`.
Same syntax as inside a process but at architecture scope; semantically
equivalent to a process with single statement.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Already consumed `<=`. Parse RHS; optional after-delay; SEMICOLON;
build CONCURRENT_SIGNAL_ASSIGN node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_concurrent_signal_assignment" that takes parser as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse concurrent signal assignment

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ASSIGN, "Expected '<=' for signal assignment"

    Let value be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after signal assignment"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_CONCURRENT_ASSIGN
    proc add_child with node, target
    proc add_child with node, value

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`label: ComponentName [generic map (...)] [port map (...)];`. Wires up
an instance of a component within an architecture.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Already have label; consume component name; optional generic map clause
(via parse_association_list); optional port map clause; expect SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_component_instantiation" that takes parser as Integer, label as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse component instantiation

    Let component_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected component name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_COMPONENT_INST
    proc set_node_value with node, "label", label
    proc set_node_value with node, "component_name", component_name

    Note: Optional generic map
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERIC:
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_MAP, "Expected 'map' after 'generic'"

        Let generic_map be proc parse_association_list with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "generic_map", generic_map
    End If

    Note: Optional port map
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PORT:
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_MAP, "Expected 'map' after 'port'"

        Let port_map be proc parse_association_list with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "port_map", port_map
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after component instantiation"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`(formal => actual, ...)` - the inside of a generic/port map. Each
entry has a formal name and the actual signal/value to bind. Positional
(without `=>`) is also allowed but mixing is restricted.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Expect LPAREN; loop parsing entries (formal name, optional `=>`,
actual expression); separator COMMA; terminator RPAREN.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_association_list" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse association list for port/generic map

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN, "Expected '(' for association list"

    Let associations be proc list_create from ListCore

    While proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN:
        Note: Parse formal => actual or positional
        Let formal be 0
        Let actual be proc parse_expression with parser

        Note: Check for named association
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARROW:
            Set formal to actual
            Set actual to proc parse_expression with parser
        End If

        Let assoc be proc create_node with NODE_ASSOCIATION
        If formal is not equal to 0:
            proc set_node_value with assoc, "formal", formal
        End If
        proc set_node_value with assoc, "actual", actual

        proc list_append from ListCore with associations, assoc

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after association list"

    Return associations
End Process

@Reasoning:
`label: for var in range generate ... end generate;` or
`label: if cond generate ... end generate;` - structural code-generation
constructs. The for-generate creates N copies; the if-generate
conditionally includes.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Already have label. Lookahead for FOR or IF; parse the appropriate
generate header; expect GENERATE; parse_concurrent_statements; expect
END GENERATE [label] SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_generate_statement" that takes parser as Integer, label as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse generate statement (for generate or if generate)

    Note: Check for for generate
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FOR:
        proc advance with parser

        Let gen_var be proc token_value with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected generate variable"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IN, "Expected 'in' after generate variable"

        Let range_start be proc parse_expression with parser

        Let direction be "to"
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TO:
            Set direction to "to"
        Otherwise If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOWNTO:
            Set direction to "downto"
        Otherwise:
            proc parser_error with parser, "Expected 'to' or 'downto' in generate range"
        End If

        Let range_end be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERATE, "Expected 'generate' after range"

        Let concurrent_stmts be proc parse_concurrent_statements with parser

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after generate"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERATE, "Expected 'generate' after 'end'"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after generate"

        Let node be proc create_node with NODE_GENERATE
        proc set_node_value with node, "label", label
        proc set_node_value with node, "type", "for"
        proc set_node_value with node, "gen_var", gen_var
        proc set_node_value with node, "range_start", range_start
        proc set_node_value with node, "range_end", range_end
        proc set_node_value with node, "direction", direction
        proc set_node_value with node, "statements", concurrent_stmts

        Return node
    End If

    Note: Check for if generate
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IF:
        proc advance with parser

        Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERATE, "Expected 'generate' after condition"

        Set concurrent_stmts to proc parse_concurrent_statements with parser

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after generate"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERATE, "Expected 'generate' after 'end'"
        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after generate"

        Set node to proc create_node with NODE_GENERATE
        proc set_node_value with node, "label", label
        proc set_node_value with node, "type", "if"
        proc set_node_value with node, "condition", condition
        proc set_node_value with node, "statements", concurrent_stmts

        Return node
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, "Expected 'for' or 'if' in generate statement"
    Return proc create_node with NODE_GENERATE
End Process

@Reasoning:
Concurrent statements (allowed at architecture scope): process,
component instantiation, concurrent signal assignment, generate.
Distinguished by lookahead - a leading label means inst or generate;
otherwise dispatch by keyword.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
If current is IDENT and peek(1) is COLON, consume label then dispatch
on next token (PROCESS, FOR/IF -> generate, IDENT -> instantiation).
Otherwise direct dispatch (PROCESS, target-IDENT for assignment).
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_concurrent_statement" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single concurrent statement

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Process statement
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCESS:
        Return proc parse_process_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Component instantiation or concurrent assignment (both start with identifier)
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        Let label_or_target be proc token_value with parser
        proc advance with parser

        Note: Check for label (identifier followed by colon)
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON:
            Let next_token be proc current_token_type with parser

            Note: For generate or if generate
            If next_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FOR:
                Return proc parse_generate_statement with parser, label_or_target
            End If
            If next_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IF:
                Return proc parse_generate_statement with parser, label_or_target
            End If

            Note: Process with label
            If next_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCESS:
                Let process_node be proc parse_process_statement with parser
                proc set_node_value with process_node, "label", label_or_target
                Return process_node
            End If

            Note: Component instantiation (label: component_name port map...)
            Return proc parse_component_instantiation with parser, label_or_target
        End If

        Note: Concurrent signal assignment (target <= value;)
        Let target_node be proc create_node with NODE_IDENTIFIER
        proc set_node_value with target_node, "name", label_or_target

        Note: Handle postfix operations on target
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let curr_type be proc current_token_type with parser

            If curr_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
                proc advance with parser
                Let index be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after index"

                Let indexed_node be proc create_node with NODE_INDEXED_NAME
                proc add_child with indexed_node, target_node
                proc add_child with indexed_node, index
                Set target_node to indexed_node
                Continue
            End If

            If curr_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOT:
                proc advance with parser
                Let field be proc token_value with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected field name"

                Let selected_node be proc create_node with NODE_SELECTED_NAME
                proc add_child with selected_node, target_node
                proc set_node_value with selected_node, "field", field
                Set target_node to selected_node
                Continue
            End If

            Break
        End While

        Return proc parse_concurrent_signal_assignment with parser, target_node
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, "Expected concurrent statement"
    Return proc create_node with NODE_NULL_STMT
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a list of concurrent statements until END (the architecture
body terminator).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop parse_concurrent_statement; break on END; append each to
STATEMENT_LIST.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_concurrent_statements" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse block of concurrent statements until end keyword

    Let statements be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        Note: Stop at end keywords
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Break
        End If

        Let stmt be proc parse_concurrent_statement with parser
        proc list_append from ListCore with statements, stmt
    End While

    Return statements
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a subprogram parameter list: the parenthesized, semicolon-separated
formal parameter interface elements of a function or procedure. Unlike a
port/generic clause, a parameter list lives entirely inside one set of
parentheses and is NOT followed by its own terminating semicolon (the
semicolon, when present, belongs to the enclosing declaration). Each
element is one-or-more comma-grouped names, a colon, an optional mode
(in/out/inout), an optional object class already consumed by the caller's
keyword (constant/variable/signal handled here when present), the subtype
indication, and an optional default value.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume LPAREN; loop until RPAREN parsing one interface element per
iteration; between elements require SEMICOLON; consume the closing RPAREN.
Returns the list of NODE_PORT_DECL parameter nodes. An empty parameter
list (immediately closing paren) yields an empty list.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_subprogram_parameter_list" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse parenthesized subprogram parameter list (no trailing semicolon)

    Let params be proc list_create from ListCore

    If proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN:
        Return params
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LPAREN, "Expected '(' before parameter list"

    While proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN:
        Let elem_token be proc current_token_type with parser
        If elem_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            proc parser_error with parser, "Unexpected end of input in parameter list"
            Break
        End If

        Note: Optional object class keyword (constant/variable/signal)
        Let object_class be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "constant"
        If elem_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CONSTANT:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If elem_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_VARIABLE:
            Set object_class to proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "variable"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If elem_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SIGNAL:
            Set object_class to proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "signal"
            proc advance with parser
        End If

        Note: One-or-more comma-separated parameter names
        Let names be proc list_create from ListCore
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let name be proc token_value with parser
            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected parameter name"
            proc list_append from ListCore with names, name

            If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON, "Expected ':' after parameter names"

        Note: Optional mode
        Let mode be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "in"
        Let mode_token be proc current_token_type with parser
        If mode_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IN:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If mode_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OUT:
            Set mode to proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "out"
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise If mode_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_INOUT:
            Set mode to proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "inout"
            proc advance with parser
        End If

        Let param_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser

        Let default_value be 0
        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL:
            Set default_value to proc parse_expression with parser
        End If

        Let param_node be proc create_node with NODE_PORT_DECL
        proc set_node_value with param_node, "names", names
        proc set_node_value with param_node, "object_class", object_class
        proc set_node_value with param_node, "mode", mode
        proc set_node_value with param_node, "subtype", param_type
        If default_value is not equal to 0:
            proc set_node_value with param_node, "default_value", default_value
        End If

        proc list_append from ListCore with params, param_node

        If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RPAREN, "Expected ')' after parameter list"

    Return params
End Process

@Reasoning:
`function Name [(parameter_list)] return Type [is declarations begin
sequential_statements end [function] [Name]] ;`. A pure VHDL function
either declares its specification only (subprogram declaration, ends at
the semicolon directly after the return type) or supplies a body (the
`is ... begin ... end` form). The parser handles both by checking for the
IS keyword after the return type.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume FUNCTION; read the designator (identifier); parse the optional
parameter list; expect RETURN; parse the return subtype indication; if IS
follows, parse the body's declarative part, BEGIN, sequential statements,
END (with optional FUNCTION keyword and designator repetition); finally
expect the terminating SEMICOLON. Attaches name, parameters, return_type
and (when present) declarations/body children onto a NODE_FUNCTION_DECL.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_function_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse VHDL function declaration or body

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION, "Expected 'function'"

    Let func_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected function name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_FUNCTION_DECL
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", func_name

    Let params be proc parse_subprogram_parameter_list with parser
    proc set_node_value with node, "parameters", params

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_RETURN, "Expected 'return' in function declaration"

    Let return_type be proc parse_subtype_indication with parser
    proc set_node_value with node, "return_type", return_type

    Note: Optional body
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS:
        Let declarations be proc parse_declarations with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "declarations", declarations

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BEGIN, "Expected 'begin' in function body"

        Let body be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "body", body

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after function body"

        Note: Optional 'function' keyword and designator repetition
        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION:
            proc advance with parser
        End If
        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
            proc advance with parser
        End If
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after function declaration"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`procedure Name [(parameter_list)] [is declarations begin
sequential_statements end [procedure] [Name]] ;`. A procedure differs from
a function only in that it has no return type. As with functions, the
specification-only and body forms are both valid, distinguished by the IS
keyword.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume PROCEDURE; read the designator; parse the optional parameter list;
if IS follows, parse the body (declarations, BEGIN, sequential statements,
END with optional PROCEDURE keyword and designator); expect the
terminating SEMICOLON. Attaches name, parameters and (when present)
declarations/body onto a NODE_PROCEDURE_DECL.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_procedure_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse VHDL procedure declaration or body

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCEDURE, "Expected 'procedure'"

    Let proc_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected procedure name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_PROCEDURE_DECL
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", proc_name

    Let params be proc parse_subprogram_parameter_list with parser
    proc set_node_value with node, "parameters", params

    Note: Optional body
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS:
        Let declarations be proc parse_declarations with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "declarations", declarations

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BEGIN, "Expected 'begin' in procedure body"

        Let body be proc parse_sequential_statements with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "body", body

        proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after procedure body"

        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCEDURE:
            proc advance with parser
        End If
        If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
            proc advance with parser
        End If
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after procedure declaration"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses the declarative part of an entity/architecture/process: signals,
variables, constants, types, subtypes, components, subprograms, etc.
Order matters because later declarations may reference earlier ones.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop dispatching by lookahead keyword (SIGNAL, VARIABLE, CONSTANT,
TYPE, SUBTYPE, COMPONENT, FUNCTION, PROCEDURE, etc.); break on BEGIN.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_declarations" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse declaration section (before begin)

    Let declarations be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        Note: Stop at begin or end
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BEGIN:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END:
            Break
        End If
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Break
        End If

        Note: Parse different declaration types
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SIGNAL:
            Let decl be proc parse_signal_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_VARIABLE:
            Set decl to proc parse_variable_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_CONSTANT:
            Set decl to proc parse_constant_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_TYPE:
            Set decl to proc parse_type_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SUBTYPE:
            Set decl to proc parse_subtype_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMPONENT:
            Set decl to proc parse_component_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Function declarations
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_FUNCTION:
            Set decl to proc parse_function_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Procedure declarations
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PROCEDURE:
            Set decl to proc parse_procedure_declaration with parser
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Unknown declaration
        proc parser_error with parser, "Expected declaration"
        proc synchronize with parser
        Break
    End While

    Return declarations
End Process

Note: ==================== Design Unit Parsing ====================

@Reasoning:
`entity Name is [generic (...)] [port (...)] [declarations] [begin
passive statements] end [entity] [Name];`. The entity defines the
external interface (ports/generics) of a hardware block.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume ENTITY; expect IDENT; expect IS; optional generic clause;
optional port clause; parse_declarations; optional BEGIN +
concurrent statements; expect END.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_entity_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse entity declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ENTITY, "Expected 'entity'"

    Let entity_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected entity name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after entity name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_ENTITY
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", entity_name

    Note: Optional generic clause
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_GENERIC:
        Let generics be proc parse_interface_list with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "generics", generics
    End If

    Note: Optional port clause
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PORT:
        Let ports be proc parse_interface_list with parser
        proc set_node_value with node, "ports", ports
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after entity"

    Note: Optional entity keyword repetition
    proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ENTITY

    Note: Optional entity name repetition
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        proc advance with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after entity declaration"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`architecture Name of EntityName is declarations begin concurrent_stmts
end [architecture] [Name];`. Implements the behavior of an entity;
multiple architectures can exist per entity for different
implementations.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume ARCHITECTURE; expect IDENT (arch name); expect OF; expect IDENT
(entity name); expect IS; parse_declarations; expect BEGIN;
parse_concurrent_statements; expect END.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_architecture_body" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse architecture body

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARCHITECTURE, "Expected 'architecture'"

    Let arch_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected architecture name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_OF, "Expected 'of' after architecture name"

    Let entity_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected entity name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after entity name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_ARCHITECTURE
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", arch_name
    proc set_node_value with node, "entity_name", entity_name

    Note: Parse declarative region
    Let declarations be proc parse_declarations with parser
    If proc list_length from ListCore with declarations is greater than 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "declarations", declarations
    End If

    Note: Parse begin
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BEGIN, "Expected 'begin' in architecture"

    Note: Parse concurrent statements
    Let statements be proc parse_concurrent_statements with parser
    proc set_node_value with node, "statements", statements

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after architecture"

    Note: Optional architecture keyword repetition
    proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARCHITECTURE

    Note: Optional architecture name repetition
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        proc advance with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after architecture body"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`package Name is declarations end [package] [Name];`. A package
exposes types, constants, components, and subprograms for use by
other design units.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume PACKAGE; expect IDENT; expect IS; parse_declarations;
expect END [PACKAGE] [IDENT] SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_package_declaration" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse package declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PACKAGE, "Expected 'package'"

    Let package_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected package name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after package name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_PACKAGE
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", package_name

    Note: Parse package declarations
    Let declarations be proc parse_declarations with parser
    If proc list_length from ListCore with declarations is greater than 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "declarations", declarations
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after package"

    Note: Optional package keyword repetition
    proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PACKAGE

    Note: Optional package name repetition
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        proc advance with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after package declaration"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`package body Name is declarations end [package body] [Name];`.
Holds the implementations of subprograms declared in the package
declaration plus deferred constants.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Consume PACKAGE BODY; expect IDENT; expect IS; parse_declarations;
expect END [PACKAGE BODY] [IDENT] SEMICOLON.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_package_body" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse package body

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PACKAGE, "Expected 'package'"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BODY, "Expected 'body' after 'package'"

    Let package_name be proc token_value with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected package name"
    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IS, "Expected 'is' after package name"

    Let node be proc create_node with NODE_PACKAGE_BODY
    proc set_node_value with node, "name", package_name

    Note: Parse package body declarations
    Let declarations be proc parse_declarations with parser
    If proc list_length from ListCore with declarations is greater than 0:
        proc set_node_value with node, "declarations", declarations
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_END, "Expected 'end' after package body"

    Note: Optional package body keyword repetition
    If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PACKAGE:
        proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BODY
    End If

    Note: Optional package name repetition
    If proc current_token_type with parser is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        proc advance with parser
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after package body"

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`library X, Y, ...; use X.Pkg.all; ...`. The library/use clauses that
precede each design unit, telling the compiler which libraries and
packages to make visible.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop while current is LIBRARY or USE: parse the appropriate clause,
expect SEMICOLON, continue.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_context_clause" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse context clause (library and use statements)

    Let context_items be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        Note: Library clause
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_LIBRARY:
            proc advance with parser

            Let node be proc create_node with NODE_LIBRARY_CLAUSE
            Let library_names be proc list_create from ListCore

            While 1 is equal to 1:
                Let lib_name be proc token_value with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected library name"
                proc list_append from ListCore with library_names, lib_name

                If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                    Break
                End If
            End While

            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after library clause"
            proc set_node_value with node, "libraries", library_names
            proc list_append from ListCore with context_items, node
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Use clause
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_USE:
            proc advance with parser

            Set node to proc create_node with NODE_USE_CLAUSE
            Let use_names be proc list_create from ListCore

            While 1 is equal to 1:
                Let use_name be proc token_value with parser
                proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected name in use clause"

                Note: Parse selected name (library.package.item)
                While proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_DOT:
                    Let next_part be proc token_value with parser
                    proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, "Expected identifier after '.'"

                    Let dot_str be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "."
                    Let combined be proc string_concat from StringPrim with use_name, dot_str
                    Set combined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with combined, next_part
                    Set use_name to combined
                End While

                proc list_append from ListCore with use_names, use_name

                If proc match_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 0:
                    Break
                End If
            End While

            proc expect_token with parser, VhdlLexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON, "Expected ';' after use clause"
            proc set_node_value with node, "names", use_names
            proc list_append from ListCore with context_items, node
            Continue
        End If

        Break
    End While

    Return context_items
End Process

@Reasoning:
A single VHDL design unit: context clause + (entity | architecture |
package | package body | configuration). The top-level program parser
loops calling this until EOF.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
parse_context_clause; lookahead keyword (ENTITY/ARCHITECTURE/PACKAGE/
CONFIGURATION); dispatch to the unit-specific parser; combine context
+ body into DESIGN_UNIT node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_design_unit" that takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single design unit (entity, architecture, package, etc.)

    Note: Parse context clause (library/use statements)
    Let context_clause be proc parse_context_clause with parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Entity declaration
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ENTITY:
        Let entity be proc parse_entity_declaration with parser
        proc set_node_value with entity, "context", context_clause
        Return entity
    End If

    Note: Architecture body
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_ARCHITECTURE:
        Let arch be proc parse_architecture_body with parser
        proc set_node_value with arch, "context", context_clause
        Return arch
    End If

    Note: Package declaration or body
    If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_PACKAGE:
        Note: Check if it's a package body
        Let next_token be proc peek_token_type with parser, 1

        If next_token is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_BODY:
            Let pkg_body be proc parse_package_body with parser
            proc set_node_value with pkg_body, "context", context_clause
            Return pkg_body
        Otherwise:
            Let pkg be proc parse_package_declaration with parser
            proc set_node_value with pkg, "context", context_clause
            Return pkg
        End If
    End If

    proc parser_error with parser, "Expected design unit (entity, architecture, or package)"
    Return proc create_node with NODE_ENTITY
End Process

Note: ==================== Main Parse Function ====================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry point. Creates the parser, loops parse_design_unit
until EOF, returns the DESIGN_FILE root containing all units.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
create_parser; build DESIGN_FILE; loop while not EOF calling
parse_design_unit and appending; return DESIGN_FILE.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse" that takes tokens as Integer, token_count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main parse function - Parse VHDL design file into AST
    Note: tokens: List of tokens from lexer
    Note: token_count: Number of tokens
    Note: Returns: Root AST node representing design file

    Let parser be proc create_parser with tokens, token_count

    Let root be proc create_node with NODE_DESIGN_FILE
    Let design_units be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Parse all design units in file
    While proc current_token_type with parser is not equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
        Let unit be proc parse_design_unit with parser
        proc list_append from ListCore with design_units, unit

        Note: Error recovery
        If parser.had_error is equal to 1:
            proc synchronize with parser
            Set parser.had_error to 0
        End If
    End While

    proc set_node_value with root, "design_units", design_units

    Return root
End Process
